description:
What is Jesus' real name? Must we stick to the original Hebrew terminology? Walter Veith explains how the New Testament addresses Jesus' real name and how this precedent helps us to understand how to refer to Jesus in our own language. Walther Veith shows explicitly that the New Testament was written in Greek and identifies how certain translations occur within the Scriptures when names are written in Aramaic or Hebrew. Walter Veith also addresses that the Old Testament name of God is virtually impossible to pronounce correctly considering the lack of knowledge of how to.
